Degree Sum Formula

The degree sum formula says that if you add up the degree of all the vertices in a (finite) graph, the result is twice the number of the edges in the graph.

Why?

Handshaking Lemma

The handshaking lemma states that the number of nodes in a graph having an odd degree is always even.

Why?

Adjacency Matrix

Tutorial: link

Perks: Check if two nodes uuu and vvv have an edge or not in O(1)O(1)O(1). Drawback: Too much space complexity for a sparse graph.

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 105;
int g[N][N];
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n, m; cin >> n >> m;
  while (m--) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    g[u][v] = 1;
    g[v][u] = 1;
  }
  if (g[4][2]) {
    cout << "YES\n";
  }
  else {
    cout << "NO\n";
  }
  return 0;
}

Connected and Disconnected Graph

If there is a path from uuu to vvv then they are connected. If all nodes are connected with each other, then the graph is connected, otherwise, disconnected. How to check if a graph is connected or not? We need to find the number of connected components.

Connected Components

A component is when each node is connected to the other one in the same component. Find the number of connected components of an undirected graph in O(V+E)O(V+E)O(V+E).

DFS

Tutorial: link

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;
vector<int> g[N];
bool vis[N];

void dfs(int u) {
  vis[u] = true;
  for (auto v: g[u]) {
    if (!vis[v]) {
      dfs(v); 
    }
  }
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n, m; cin >> n >> m;
  while (m--) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    g[u].push_back(v);
    g[v].push_back(u);
  }
  // dfs(1);
  // for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
  //   if (!vis[i]) {
  //     cout << "Disconnected Graph\n";
  //     return 0;
  //   }
  // }
  // cout << "Connected Graph\n";
  int ans = 0;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    if (!vis[i]) {
      dfs(i);
      ++ans;
    }
  }
  cout << "Connected Components = " << ans << '\n';
  return 0;
}

BFS

Tutorial: link

Problem: Given an undirected unweighted graph with nnn nodes, find the shortest path from 111 to nnn in O(V+E)O(V + E)O(V+E). How to extract the shortest path?

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;
vector<int> g[N];
bool vis[N]; int dis[N], par[N];

int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n, m; cin >> n >> m;
  while (m--) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    g[u].push_back(v);
    g[v].push_back(u);
  }
  queue<int> q;
  q.push(1); vis[1] = true; dis[1] = 0;
  while (!q.empty()) {
    int u = q.front();
    q.pop();
    for (auto v: g[u]) {
      if (!vis[v]) {
        q.push(v);
        par[v] = u;
        dis[v] = dis[u] + 1;
        vis[v] = true;
      }
    }
  }
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    cout << dis[i] << ' ';
  }
  cout << '\n';
  int v = 4;
  while (v != 1) {
    cout << v << ' ';
    v = par[v];
  }
  cout << 1 << '\n';
}

Bicoloring and Bipartite Graphs

A Bipartite Graph is a graph whose vertices can be divided into two independent sets, U and V such that every edge (u, v) either connects a vertex from U to V or a vertex from V to U. In other words, for every edge (u, v), either u belongs to U and v to V, or u belongs to V and v to U.

This is the same as coloring the graph in two colors such that every adjacent node has different colors.

How to check if a graph is bipartite or not?

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;
vector<int> g[N];
bool vis[N]; int col[N];
bool ok;

void dfs(int u) {
  vis[u] = true;
  for (auto v: g[u]) {
    if (!vis[v]) {
      col[v] = col[u] ^ 1;
      dfs(v); 
    }
    else {
      if (col[u] == col[v]) {
        ok = false;
      }
    }
  }
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n, m; cin >> n >> m;
  while (m--) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    g[u].push_back(v);
    g[v].push_back(u);
  }
  ok = true;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    if (!vis[i]) dfs(i);
  }
  if (ok) {
    cout << "YES\n";
  }
  else {
    cout << "NO\n";
  }
}

Finding A Cycle

  • How to check if an undirected graph has a cycle or not?
  • How to check if a directed graph has a cycle or not?

Tutorial: link

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;
vector<int> g[N];
int col[N], par[N];
bool cycle;
void dfs(int u) {
  col[u] = 1;
  for (auto v: g[u]) {
    if (col[v] == 0) {
      par[v] = u;
      dfs(v);
    }
    else if (col[v] == 1) {
      cycle = true;
      // you can track the cycle using par array
    }
  }
  col[u] = 2;
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n, m; cin >> n >> m;
  for (int i = 1; i <= m; i++) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    g[u].push_back(v); 
  }
  cycle = false;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    if (col[i] == 0) dfs(i);
  }
  cout << (cycle ? "YES\n" : "NO\n") << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Topological Sorting

Tutorial: link1, link2

O(V2)O(V^2)O(V2) code:

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;
int indeg[N];
vector<int> g[N];
bool vis[N];
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n, m; cin >> n >> m;
  while (m--) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    indeg[v]++;
    g[u].push_back(v);
  }
  vector<int> ans;
  while (ans.size() < n) {
    int cur = 0;
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
      if (!vis[i] and indeg[i] == 0) {
        cur = i;
        break;
      }
    }
    if (cur == 0) {
      cout << "IMPOSSIBLE\n";
      return 0;
    }
    vis[cur] = true;
    ans.push_back(cur);
    for (auto v: g[cur]) {
      indeg[v]--;
    }
  }
  for (auto x: ans) cout << x << ' ';
  return 0;
}

Using DFS in O(V+E)O(V + E)O(V+E):

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;
int indeg[N];
vector<int> g[N];
bool vis[N];
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n, m; cin >> n >> m;
  while (m--) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    indeg[v]++;
    g[u].push_back(v);
  }
  vector<int> z;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    if (indeg[i] == 0) {
      z.push_back(i);
      vis[i] = true;
    }
  }
  vector<int> ans;
  while (ans.size() < n) {
    if (z.empty()) {
      cout << "IMPOSSIBLE\n";
      return 0;
    }
    int cur = z.back();
    z.pop_back();
    ans.push_back(cur);
    for (auto v: g[cur]) {
      indeg[v]--;
      if (!vis[v] and indeg[v] == 0) {
        z.push_back(v);
        vis[v] = true;
      }
    }
  }
  for (auto x: ans) cout << x << ' ';
  return 0;
}

Trees

A tree is one kind of graph that is acyclic and there is exactly one path between every pair of nodes.

Definitions:

  • Tree
  • Rooted Tree
  • Root
  • Parent
  • Child
  • Leaf

Q: How many edges does a tree with nnn nodes contain?

Q: If we delete an edge from a tree, how many connected components will it divide into?

Btw what is a rooted tree?

Problem: Find the depth of all nodes in a rooted tree.

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

vector<int> g[105];
int dep[105];
void dfs(int u, int p) {
  dep[u] = dep[p] + 1;
  for (auto v: g[u]) {
    if (v != p) {
      dfs(v, u);
    }
  }
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n; cin >> n;
  for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    g[u].push_back(v);
    g[v].push_back(u);
  }
  dfs(1, 0);
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    cout << dep[i] << ' ';
  }
  return 0;
}

Diameter of a Tree

Tutorial: link

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;
vector<int> g[N];
int dep[N];
int mx, node, ans;
void dfs1(int u, int p) {
  dep[u] = dep[p] + 1;
  if (dep[u] > mx) {
    mx = dep[u];
    node = u;
  }
  for (auto v: g[u]) {
    if (v != p) {
      dfs1(v, u);
    }
  }
}
void dfs2(int u, int p) {
  dep[u] = dep[p] + 1;
  ans = max(ans, dep[u] - 1);
  for (auto v: g[u]) {
    if (v != p) {
      dfs2(v, u);
    }
  }
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n; cin >> n;
  for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    g[u].push_back(v);
    g[v].push_back(u);
  }
  dfs1(1, 0);
  dfs2(node, 0);
  cout << ans << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Also, the same algorithm works for weighted trees too!

2. Problem B

Editorial: N/A

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
const int N = 105;
vector <int> adj[N];
bool vis[N];
int tim, fv[N], dt[N];
void dfs(int node) {
    vis[node] = 1;
    fv[node] = tim++;
    for (int i = 0; i < adj[node].size(); i++) {
        int chld = adj[node][i];
        if (!vis[chld]) {
            dfs(chld);
        }
    }
    dt[node] = tim++;
}
int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    tim = 1;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        int id, k;
        cin >> id >> k;
        for (int j = 0; j < k; j++)
        {
            int chld;
            cin >> chld;
            adj[id].push_back(chld);
        }
    }
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (!vis[i]) dfs(i);
    }
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++)
        cout << i << " " << fv[i] << " " << dt[i] << '\n';
}

3. Problem C

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
#define ll long long
using namespace std;
const int N = 205;
vector <int> adj[N];
bool vis[N], flg;
int clr[N];
void dfs(int node) {
    vis[node] = 1;
    for (int i = 0; i < adj[node].size(); i++) {
        int chld = adj[node][i];
        if (!vis[chld]) {
            clr[chld] = clr[node] ^ 1;
            dfs(chld);
        }
        if (clr[chld] == clr[node]) {
            flg = 0;
        }
    }
}
int main()
{
    while (1) {
        memset(vis, 0, sizeof(vis));
        memset(clr, 0, sizeof(clr));
        int n;
        cin >> n;
        if (!n) break;
        int m;
        cin >> m;
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            int u, v;
            cin >> u >> v;
            adj[u].push_back(v);
            adj[v].push_back(u);
        }
        flg = 1;
        dfs(0);
        if (flg) cout << "BICOLORABLE.\n";
        else cout << "NOT BICOLORABLE.\n";
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) adj[i].clear();
    }
}

4. Problem D

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
#define ll long long
using namespace std;
const int N = 35;
vector <int> adj[N];
bool vis[N];
int dis[N];
queue <int> qu;
int res, sz;
void bfs(int mxdis) {
    while (qu.size()) {
        int node = qu.front();
        qu.pop();
        sz++;
        vis[node] = 1;
        for (int i = 0; i < adj[node].size(); i++) {
            int chld = adj[node][i];
            if (!vis[chld]) {
                qu.push(chld);
                vis[chld] = 1;
                dis[chld] = dis[node] + 1;
                if (dis[chld] > mxdis) {
                    res++;
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
int main()
{
    int cs = 0;
    while (1) {
        int n;
        cin >> n;
        if (!n) break;
        map <ll, ll> mark;
        map <ll, ll> :: iterator it;
        int c = 1;
        vector <pair<ll, ll> > pr;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            ll u, v;
            cin >> u >> v;
            pr.push_back(make_pair(u, v));
            if (!mark[u]) mark[u] = c++;
            if (!mark[v]) mark[v] = c++;
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int u = mark[pr[i].first];
            int v = mark[pr[i].second];
            adj[u].push_back(v);
            adj[v].push_back(u);
        }
        while (1) {
            int node, len;
            cin >> node >> len;
            if (!node && !len) break;
            memset(vis, 0, sizeof(vis));
            memset(dis, 0, sizeof(dis));
            res = 0;
            sz = 0;
            qu.push(mark[node]);
            bfs(len);
            res += (mark.size() - sz);
            cout << "Case " << ++cs << ": ";
            printf("%d nodes not reachable from node %d with TTL = %d.\n", res, node, len);
        }
        for (int i = 1; i <= 31; i++) adj[i].clear();
    }
}

5. Problem E

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
const int N = 1e5 + 5;
vector <int> adj[N];
bool vis[N];
int a[N], deg[N];
int n, m, res;
void solve(int node, int ct, int mxct) {
    vis[node] = 1;
    if (node > 1 && deg[node] == 1 && mxct <= m) {
        res++;
    }
    for (int i = 0; i < adj[node].size(); i++) {
        int chld = adj[node][i];
        if (!vis[chld]) {
            int mx = max(mxct, ct + a[chld]);
            if (a[chld]) {
                solve(chld, ct + 1, mx);
            }
            else solve(chld, 0, mx);
        }
    }
}
int main() {
    cin >> n >> m;
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) cin >> a[i];
    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        int u, v;
        cin >> u >> v;
        adj[u].push_back(v);
        adj[v].push_back(u);
        deg[u]++;
        deg[v]++;
    }
    if (a[1]) solve(1, 1, 1);
    else solve(1, 0, 0);
    cout << res << '\n';
}

6. Problem F

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
const int N = 105;
bool vis[N];
vector <int> adj[N];
int c1;
int cst[N][N], ans = 1e9;
void dfs(int n, int par) {
    if (n == 1 && par != -1) {
        ans = min(ans, c1);
        c1 = 0;
        return;
    }
    for (int i = 0; i < adj[n].size(); i++) {
        int chld = adj[n][i];
        if (chld != par) {
            c1 += cst[n][chld];
            dfs(chld, n);
        }
    }
}
int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    int ttl = 0;
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        int u, v, c;
        cin >> u >> v >> c;
        adj[u].push_back(v);
        adj[v].push_back(u);
        cst[u][v] = 0;
        cst[v][u] = c;
        ttl += c;
    }
    dfs(1, -1);
    cout << ans << '\n';
}

7. Problem G

Editorial: N/A

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
#define ll long long
using namespace std;
const int N = 105;
vector <int> adj[N];
bool vis[N];
int dis[N];
queue <int> qu;
void bfs() {
    while (qu.size()) {
        int node = qu.front();
        qu.pop();
        vis[node] = 1;
        for (int i = 0; i < adj[node].size(); i++) {
            int chld = adj[node][i];
            if (!vis[chld]) {
                qu.push(chld);
                vis[chld] = 1;
                dis[chld] = dis[node] + 1;
            }
        }
    }
}
int main()
{
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        int id, k;
        cin >> id >> k;
        for (int j = 0; j < k; j++) {
            int v;
            cin >> v;
            adj[id].push_back(v);
        }
    }
    qu.push(1);
    bfs();
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {

13. Problem M

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
#define ll long long
using namespace std;
ll calc(string s, ll m) {
    ll ret = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) {
        ret = ((ret * 10) + (s[i] - '0')) % m;
    }
    return ret;
}
string inttostr(ll x) {
    string ret;
    if (!x) return "0";
    while (x) {
        ret += ((x%10) + '0');
        x /= 10;
    }
    return ret;
}
bool iszer(string s) {
    for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) {
        if (s[i] != '0') return false;
    }
    return true;
}
int main() {
    ll n, sz, cs = 0;
    while (scanf("%lld %lld", &n, &sz) != EOF) {
        map <int, int> mark;
        for (int i = 0; i < sz; i++) {
            int x;
            cin >> x;
            mark[x] = 1;
        }
        ll num = n, f = 1;
        while (num) {
            if (mark[num % 10]) {f = 0;break;}
            num /= 10;
        }
        if (f) {
            cout << "Case " << ++cs << ": ";
            cout << n << '\n';
            continue;
        }
        vector <int> alwd;
        for (int i = 0; i <= 9; i++) {
            if (!mark[i]) alwd.push_back(i);
        }
        queue <string> qu;
        for (int i = 0; i < alwd.size(); i++) {
           if (alwd[i]) qu.push(inttostr(alwd[i]));
        }
        bool flg = 0;
        string ans = "-1";
        int vis[n + 5];
        memset(vis, 0, sizeof(vis));
        while (!qu.empty()) {
            string str = qu.front();
            qu.pop();
            ll s = calc(str, n);
            if (!s) {
                ans = str;
                break;
            }
            if (!vis[s]) {
                    vis[s] = 1;
                for (int i = 0; i < alwd.size(); i++) {
                    string str1 = str + inttostr(alwd[i]);
                    qu.push(str1);
                }
            }
        }
        cout << "Case " << ++cs << ": ";
        for (int i = 0; i < ans.size(); i++) {
            if (!i && ans[i] == '0') {
                while (ans[i] == '0') i++;
            }
            cout << ans[i];
        }
        cout << '\n';
    }
}

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
const int N = 105;
int indeg[N];
vector <int> adj[N];
int main() {
    while (1) {
        memset(indeg, 0, sizeof(indeg));
        int n, m;
        cin >> n >> m;
        if (!n && !m) break;
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            int u, v;
            cin >> u >> v;
            indeg[v]++;
            adj[u].push_back(v);
        }
        vector <int> v;
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            if (!indeg[i]) {
                v.push_back(i);
            }
        }
        vector <int> ans;
        while (ans.size() < n) {
            if (!v.size()) {
                cout << -1 << '\n';
                break;
            }
            int cur = v.back();
            v.pop_back();
            ans.push_back(cur);
            for (int i = 0; i < adj[cur].size(); i++) {
                int chld = adj[cur][i];
                indeg[chld]--;
                if (!indeg[chld]) {
                    v.push_back(chld);
                }
            }
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < ans.size(); i++) {
            cout << ans[i] << " ";
        }
        cout << '\n';
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) adj[i].clear();
    }
}

        int chld = adj[node][i];

        }

        int u, v;

        adj[v].push_back(u);
    }

    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (i & 1) {
            ans += (ev * cnt[i]);
            od += cnt[i];
        }
        else {
            ans += (od * cnt[i]);
            ev += cnt[i];
        }
    }

}

19. Problem S

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
#define ll long long
using namespace std;
const int N = 2e5 + 5;
ll inf = 1e18;
ll dis[N], vis[N], ans[N];
vector <int> adj[N];
int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    int a[n + 2];
    queue <int> qu;
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        cin >> a[i];
        if (i + a[i] <= n) {
            adj[i + a[i]].push_back(i);
        }
        if (i - a[i] >= 1) {
            adj[i - a[i]].push_back(i);
        }
    }
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) dis[i] = inf;
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (a[i] % 2 == 0) {
            qu.push(i);
            dis[i] = 0;
        }
    }
    while (!qu.empty()) {
        int x = qu.front();
        qu.pop();
        for (int i = 0; i < adj[x].size(); i++) {
            int chld = adj[x][i];
            if (dis[chld] == inf) {
                dis[chld] = dis[x] + 1;
                qu.push(chld);
            }
        }
    }
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (a[i] % 2) ans[i] = dis[i];
    }
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) dis[i] = inf;
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (a[i] % 2 == 1) {
            qu.push(i);
            dis[i] = 0;
        }
    }
    while (!qu.empty()) {
        int x = qu.front();
        qu.pop();
        for (int i = 0; i < adj[x].size(); i++) {
            int chld = adj[x][i];
            if (dis[chld] == inf) {
                dis[chld] = dis[x] + 1;
                qu.push(chld);
            }
        }
    }
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (a[i] % 2 == 0) {
            ans[i] = dis[i];
        }
    }
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (ans[i] != inf) cout << ans[i] << " ";
        else cout << -1 << " ";
    }
    cout << '\n';
}

20. Problem T

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
#define ll long long
using namespace std;
int main() {
    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;
    ll a[n + 2];
    map <ll, ll> mark, lvl;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> a[i];
        mark[a[i]] = 1;
    }
    sort (a, a + n);
    queue <ll> qu;
    ll sum = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (!i || a[i] - a[i - 1] != 1) {
            if (!mark[a[i] - 1]) {
                qu.push(a[i] - 1);
                lvl[a[i] - 1] = 1;
                mark[a[i] - 1] = 1;
            }
        }
        if (i == n - 1 || a[i + 1] - a[i] != 1) {
            if (!mark[a[i] + 1]) {
                qu.push(a[i] + 1);
                lvl[a[i] + 1] = 1;
                mark[a[i] + 1] = 1;
            }
        }
    }
    vector <int> ans;
    while (ans.size() < m) {
        ll x = qu.front();
        qu.pop();
        ans.push_back(x);
        sum += lvl[x];
        if (!mark[x + 1]) {
            qu.push(x + 1);
            lvl[x + 1] = lvl[x] + 1;
            mark[x + 1] = 1;
        }
        if (!mark[x - 1]) {
            qu.push(x - 1);
            lvl[x - 1] = lvl[x] + 1;
            mark[x - 1] = 1;
        }
    }
    cout << sum << '\n';
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) cout << ans[i] << " ";
    cout << '\n';
}

    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;
    char grid[n + 2][m + 2];
    int stx, sty, ndx, ndy;
    queue <pair<int, int> > qu;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
            cin >> grid[i][j];
            if (grid[i][j] == 'A') {
                stx = i, sty = j;
                qu.push({i, j});
            }
            if (grid[i][j] == 'B') {
                ndx = i, ndy = j;
            }
        }
    }
    //map <pair<int, int>, int> dis;
    map <pair<int, int>, pair<int, int> > parnt;
    while (!qu.empty()) {
        int x = qu.front().first, y = qu.front().second;
        qu.pop();
        vis[x][y] = 1;
        if (y + 1 < m && !vis[x][y + 1] && grid[x][y + 1] != '#') {
            qu.push({x, y + 1});
            //dis[{x, y + 1}] = dis[{x, y}] + 1;
            dis[x][y + 1] = dis[x][y] + 1;
            vis[x][y + 1] = 1;
            parnt[{x, y + 1}] = {x, y};
        }
        if (y - 1 >= 0 && !vis[x][y - 1] && grid[x][y - 1] != '#') {
            qu.push({x, y - 1});
            //dis[{x, y - 1}] = dis[{x, y}] + 1;
            dis[x][y - 1] = dis[x][y] + 1;
            vis[x][y - 1] = 1;
            parnt[{x, y - 1}] = {x, y};
        }
        if (x + 1 < n && !vis[x + 1][y] && grid[x + 1][y] != '#') {
            qu.push({x + 1, y});
            //dis[{x + 1, y}] = dis[{x, y}] + 1;
            dis[x + 1][y] = dis[x][y] + 1;
            vis[x + 1][y] = 1;
            parnt[{x + 1, y}] = {x, y};
        }
        if (x - 1 >= 0 && !vis[x - 1][y] && grid[x - 1][y] != '#') {
            qu.push({x - 1, y});
            //dis[{x - 1, y}] = dis[{x, y}] + 1;
            dis[x - 1][y] = dis[x][y] + 1;
            parnt[{x - 1, y}] = {x, y};
            vis[x - 1][y] = 1;
        }
    }
    if (!vis[ndx][ndy]) cout << "NO\n";
    else {
        cout << "YES" << '\n';
        cout << dis[ndx][ndy] << '\n';
        string res;
        while (ndx != stx || ndy != sty) {
            int x = parnt[{ndx, ndy}].first;
            int y = parnt[{ndx, ndy}].second;
            if (x == ndx + 1) {
                res += "U";
            }
            if (x == ndx - 1) {
                res += "D";
            }
            if (y == ndy + 1) {
                res += "L";
            }
            if (y == ndy - 1) {
                res += "R";
            }
            ndx = x;
            ndy = y;
        }
        reverse(res.begin(), res.end());
        cout << res << '\n';
    }
}

23. CSES 1666: Building Roads

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
const int N = 1e5 + 9;
vector <int> adj[N];
bool vis[N];
void dfs(int n) {
    vis[n] = 1;
    for (int i = 0; i < adj[n].size(); i++) {
        int chld = adj[n][i];
        if (!vis[chld]) {
            dfs(chld);
        }
    }
}
int main() {
    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        int u, v;
        cin >> u >> v;
        adj[u].push_back(v);
        adj[v].push_back(u);
    }
    vector <int> v;
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (!vis[i]) {
            dfs(i);
            v.push_back(i);
        }
    }
    cout << v.size() - 1 << '\n';
    for (int i = 0; i < v.size() - 1; i++) {
        cout << v[i] << " " << v[i + 1] << '\n';
    }
}

24. CSES 1667: Message Route

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
const int N = 1e5 + 9;
bool vis[N];
vector <int> adj[N];
int dis[N], par[N];
int main() {
    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        int u, v;
        cin >> u >> v;
        adj[u].push_back(v);
        adj[v].push_back(u);
    }
    queue <int> qu;
    qu.push(1);
    dis[1] = 1;
    while (!qu.empty()) {
        int node = qu.front();
        qu.pop();
        for (int i = 0; i < adj[node].size(); i++) {
            int chld = adj[node][i];
            if (!vis[chld]) {
                dis[chld] = dis[node] + 1;
                par[chld] = node;
                qu.push(chld);
                vis[chld] = 1;
            }
        }
    }
    if (vis[n]) {
        cout << dis[n] << '\n';
        vector <int> v;
        int x = n;
        v.push_back(n);
        while (x != 1) {
            x = par[x];
            v.push_back(x);
        }
        reverse(v.begin(), v.end());
        for (int i = 0; i < v.size(); i++) cout << v[i] << ' ';
        cout << '\n';
    }
    else cout << "IMPOSSIBLE\n";
}

25. CSES 1669: Round Trip I

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
const int N = 1e5 + 9;
vector <int> adj[N];
bool vis[N], fnd = 0;
int par[N];
vector <int> v;
void dfs(int n, int p) {
    vis[n] = 1;
    for (int i = 0; i < adj[n].size(); i++) {
        int chld = adj[n][i];
        if (!vis[chld]) {
            vis[chld] = 1;
            par[chld] = n;
            dfs(chld, n);
        }
        else if (chld != p && !fnd) {
            int x = chld;
            fnd = 1;
            v.push_back(n);
            while (n != x) {
                n = par[n];
                if (n == 0) break;
                v.push_back(n);
            }
            v.push_back(v[0]);
        }
    }
}
int main() {
    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        int u, v;
        cin >> u >> v;
        adj[u].push_back(v);
        adj[v].push_back(u);
    }
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (!vis[i] && !fnd) dfs(i, 0);
    }
    if (!v.size()) {
        cout << "IMPOSSIBLE\n";
    }
    else {
        cout << v.size() << '\n';
        for (int i = 0; i < v.size(); i++) cout << v[i] << ' ';
        cout << '\n';
    }
}

26. CSES 1678: Round Trip II

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
#define ll long long
using namespace std;
const int N = 1e5 + 9;
int clr[N], par[N];
bool fnd = 0;
vector <int> v;
vector <int> adj[N];
void dfs(int n) {
    clr[n] = 1;
    for (int i = 0; i < adj[n].size(); i++) {
        int chld = adj[n][i];
        if (!clr[chld]) {
            clr[chld] = 1;
            par[chld] = n;
            dfs(chld);
        }
        else if(clr[chld] == 1 && !fnd) {
            int x = chld;
            v.push_back(chld);
            v.push_back(n);
            while (x != n) {
                n = par[n];
                v.push_back(n);
                fnd = 1;
            }
            reverse(v.begin(), v.end());
        }
    }
    clr[n] = 2;
}
int main() {
    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        int u, v;
        cin >> u >> v;
        adj[u].push_back(v);
    }
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (!clr[i] && !fnd) {
            dfs(i);
        }
    }
    if (fnd) {
        cout << v.size() << '\n';
        for (int i = 0; i < v.size(); i++) cout << v[i] << ' ';
        cout << '\n';
    }
    else cout << "IMPOSSIBLE\n";
}

27. CSES 1679: Course Schedule

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
#define ll long long
using namespace std;
const int N = 1e5 + 9;
vector <int> v, res;
vector <int> adj[N];
int indeg[N];
int main() {
    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        int u, v;
        cin >> u >> v;
        adj[u].push_back(v);
        indeg[v]++;
    }
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (!indeg[i]) {
            v.push_back(i);
        }
    }
    bool fnd = 1;
    while (res.size() != n) {
        if (v.size() == 0) {
            fnd = 0;
            break;
        }
        int node = v.back();
        v.pop_back();
        res.push_back(node);
        for (int i = 0; i < adj[node].size(); i++) {
            int chld = adj[node][i];
            indeg[chld]--;
            if (!indeg[chld]) v.push_back(chld);
        }
    }
    if (fnd) {
        for (int i = 0; i < res.size(); i++) cout << res[i] << ' ';
        cout << '\n';
    }
    else cout << "IMPOSSIBLE\n";
}

28. CSES 1194: Monsters

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
const int N = 1e3 + 9;
bool vis[N][N];
int dis[N][N],dis1[N][N];
int main() {
    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;
    char grid[n + 2][m + 2];
    queue <pair<int, int> > qu;
    int ax, ay;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
            cin >> grid[i][j];
            if (grid[i][j] == 'M') {
                qu.push({i, j});
            }
            if (grid[i][j] == 'A') {
                ax = i, ay = j;
            }
        }
    }
    if (!ax || ax == n - 1 || !ay || ay == m - 1) {
        cout << "YES\n";
        cout << 0 << '\n';
        return 0;
    }
    while (!qu.empty()) {
        int x = qu.front().first;
        int y = qu.front().second;
        qu.pop();
        vis[x][y] = 1;
        if (y + 1 < m && !vis[x][y + 1] && grid[x][y + 1] == '.') {
            qu.push({x, y + 1});
            dis[x][y + 1] = dis[x][y] + 1;
            vis[x][y + 1] = 1;
        }
        if (y - 1 >= 0 && !vis[x][y - 1] && grid[x][y - 1] == '.') {
            qu.push({x, y - 1});
            dis[x][y - 1] = dis[x][y] + 1;
            vis[x][y - 1] = 1;
        }
        if (x + 1 < n && !vis[x + 1][y] && grid[x + 1][y] == '.') {
            qu.push({x + 1, y});
            dis[x + 1][y] = dis[x][y] + 1;
            vis[x + 1][y] = 1;
        }
        if (x - 1 >= 0 && !vis[x - 1][y] && grid[x - 1][y] == '.') {
            qu.push({x - 1, y});
            dis[x - 1][y] = dis[x][y] + 1;
            vis[x - 1][y] = 1;
        }
    }
    qu.push({ax, ay});
    map <pair<int,int>, pair<int, int> > par;
    memset(vis, 0, sizeof(vis));
    while (!qu.empty()) {
        int x = qu.front().first;
        int y = qu.front().second;
        qu.pop();
        vis[x][y] = 1;
        if (y + 1 < m && !vis[x][y + 1] && grid[x][y + 1] == '.') {
            qu.push({x, y + 1});
            dis1[x][y + 1] = dis1[x][y] + 1;
            vis[x][y + 1] = 1;
            par[{x, y + 1}] = {x, y};
        }
        if (y - 1 >= 0 && !vis[x][y - 1] && grid[x][y - 1] == '.') {
            qu.push({x, y - 1});
            dis1[x][y - 1] = dis1[x][y] + 1;
            vis[x][y - 1] = 1;
            par[{x, y - 1}] = {x, y};
        }
        if (x + 1 < n && !vis[x + 1][y] && grid[x + 1][y] == '.') {
            qu.push({x + 1, y});
            dis1[x + 1][y] = dis1[x][y] + 1;
            vis[x + 1][y] = 1;
            par[{x + 1, y}] = {x, y};
        }
        if (x - 1 >= 0 && !vis[x - 1][y] && grid[x - 1][y] == '.') {
            qu.push({x - 1, y});
            dis1[x - 1][y] = dis1[x][y] + 1;
            vis[x - 1][y] = 1;
            par[{x - 1, y}] = {x, y};
        }
    }
    bool fnd = 0;
    int dx, dy;
    for (int i = 0; i < n && !fnd; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < m && !fnd; j++) {
            if ((!i || i == n - 1 || !j || j == m - 1) && grid[i][j] == '.') {
                if (!dis[i][j] && dis1[i][j]) {
                    fnd = 1;
                    dx = i, dy = j;
                }
                else if (dis[i][j] && dis1[i][j] && dis[i][j] > dis1[i][j]) {
                    fnd = 1;
                    dx = i, dy = j;
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
    }
    if (fnd) {
        cout << "YES\n";
        string res;
        while (dx != ax || dy != ay) {
            int x = par[{dx, dy}].first;
            int y = par[{dx, dy}].second;
            if (y - dy == 1) {
                res += "L";
            }
            else if (dy - y == 1) {
                res += "R";
            }
            else if (dx - x == 1) {
                res += "D";
            }
            else if (x - dx == 1) {
                res += "U";
            }
            dx = x, dy = y;
        }
        reverse(res.begin(), res.end());
        cout << res.size() << '\n';
        cout << res << '\n';
    }
    else cout << "NO\n";
}
